The teen suspects arrested in connection with the death of Kulani Mathebula will appear at the Johannesburg Magistrate’s Court on Friday. Nineteen-year-old Mathebula died earlier this month after he was stabbed while walking to school in Mondeor, south of Johannesburg. The suspects are aged between 13 and 15-years-old. Police Spokesperson Kay Makhubele says: “The two boys who were charged with murder of a learner in Mondeor High will be appearing in the Johannesburg Magistrate’s Court and we are continuing with our investigation.” Watch the video below for related news:  